description.narrative: The humanitarian needs of 561,784 children were met[1], despite receiving twenty-two percent[2]of the HAC requirement. Internal displacements now affect nine of Cameroon’s 10 regions. The North-west, South-west, Far North, North, Adamawa and East regions are the most vulnerable.UNICEF is supporting the localization agenda in-country, maintaining existing partnerships with 27 local NGOs, up from 26 in 2000 delivering results for the hardest–to–reach children. A Child Risk Impact Analysis has been finalized. The Country Office met EPP compliance and Field Office Emergency Preparedness has been fast-tracked.;[1]As of October 2021. SAM results, August 2021[2]At September 2021 | Status:Met | As-of Date:02/02/2022
